---
import Layout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Navigation } from '../components/Navigation';
import { FooterExpanded } from '../components/homepage/FooterExpanded';
---

<Layout title="Methodology - HealthFees.org">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-white">
    <Navigation client:load />
    
    <main class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Our Methodology</h1>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            Understanding how we collect, process, and present healthcare pricing data to ensure 
            accuracy and transparency.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Data Sources</h2>
          <p>
            Our pricing data comes from multiple sources mandated by federal transparency regulations:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Hospital Price Transparency Files:</strong> Machine-readable files published by hospitals containing standard charges</li>
            <li><strong>Insurance Company Transparency Files:</strong> In-network negotiated rates published by insurers</li>
            <li><strong>Medicare & Medicaid Data:</strong> Publicly available government reimbursement rates</li>
            <li><strong>Cash Price Data:</strong> Self-pay prices published by healthcare providers</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Data Collection Process</h2>
          <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">1. Automated Extraction</h3>
            <p>
              We automatically download and process thousands of price transparency files 
              published by hospitals and insurers across the United States.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">2. Data Standardization</h3>
            <p>
              Raw data is cleaned and standardized to ensure consistency across different 
              providers and billing code systems (CPT, HCPCS, DRG).
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">3. Quality Assurance</h3>
            <p>
              Multiple validation checks identify and filter out incomplete, outdated, 
              or erroneous pricing information.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Accuracy & Limitations</h2>
          <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-900 mb-2">Important Notes</h3>
            <ul class="text-yellow-800 space-y-2">
              <li>• Prices shown are estimates based on published rates</li>
              <li>• Actual costs may vary based on individual circumstances</li>
              <li>• Data is updated regularly but may not reflect real-time changes</li>
              <li>• Some providers may not publish complete pricing information</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Update Frequency</h2>
          <p>
            We update our database on a rolling basis:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Daily:</strong> High-volume providers and major insurance companies</li>
            <li><strong>Weekly:</strong> Mid-size hospitals and regional insurers</li>
            <li><strong>Monthly:</strong> Smaller providers and specialized facilities</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Privacy & Security</h2>
          <p>
            All data we collect is from publicly available sources required by law. 
            We do not collect or store any personal health information (PHI) or 
            individually identifiable data.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Questions About Our Methodology?</h2>
          <p>
            For detailed questions about our data collection and processing methods, 
            <a href="/contact" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">contact our research team</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    
    <FooterExpanded client:load />
  </div>
</Layout>
